question.en:
Consider a payment processing system. You have a PaymentProcessor base class, with subclasses CreditCardPayment and CryptoPayment. The base class expects a 3-digit CVV, but CryptoPayment does not use CVV. What principle is violated when CryptoPayment throws an error for the missing CVV?
```js
class PaymentProcessor {
  process(amount, cvv) {
    if (!cvv || cvv.length !== 3) throw new Error('Invalid CVV');
  }
}

class CryptoPayment extends PaymentProcessor {
  process(amount, cvv) {
    // CryptoPayment doesn't need CVV, but must accept it
    super.process(amount, cvv); // Throws error!
  }
}
```

